# WaveX Rhythm Game - Project Overview

WaveX is a complete HTML5 rhythm game inspired by OSU!Mania with a modern arcade feel. The game features four-key vertical scrolling gameplay using D, F, J, K controls.

## Core Architecture

### Main Files
- [index.html](mdc:index.html) - Main game structure with UI screens and modals
- [style.css](mdc:style.css) - Dark futuristic UI styling with neon highlights
- [script.js](mdc:script.js) - Complete game logic, audio management, and UI rendering
- [server.js](mdc:server.js) - Node.js backend for file uploads and chart storage
- [package.json](mdc:package.json) - Project dependencies and scripts

### Key Features
- **Play Mode**: Song selection, scoring system (Perfect/Great/Good/Miss), combo tracking
- **Chart Editor**: MP3 loading, note placement during playback, timeline visualization
- **Community System**: Chart publishing, rating, downloading, and sharing
- **Admin Panel**: Password-protected song management and deletion
- **Progression System**: XP/Level, achievements, leaderboards, modifiers

### Tech Stack
- **Frontend**: HTML5 Canvas, Web Audio API, localStorage
- **Backend**: Node.js + Express, Multer for file uploads
- **Storage**: Server-side chart persistence, client-side profile/options
- **Deployment**: GitHub Pages (frontend) + Render (backend)

## Development Guidelines
- All JavaScript is encapsulated in an IIFE to prevent global scope pollution
- Audio loading supports multiple formats: data URLs, HTTP URLs, local paths
- Extensive console logging for debugging audio and chart loading issues
- Responsive design with mobile-friendly controls
- Security: Admin passwords stored as bcrypt hashes, session tokens for authentication
